1. Derived Query Methods by Naming Strategies

Theory
Spring Data JPA lets you create queries just by naming your repository methods in a certain way.
It parses the method name and generates the SQL/JPQL for you.

Common Naming Patterns

Comparison:
findByAgeGreaterThan(int age) → Finds entities where age > given value.

Case-insensitive:
findByNameIgnoreCase(String name) → Ignores case when matching name.

Logical operators:
findByNameAndStatus(String name, Status status) → Combines conditions.

Ordering:
findByStatusOrderByAgeDesc(Status status) → Orders results.

Implementation
Repository Example:

public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {
    List<User> findByAgeGreaterThan(int age);
    List<User> findByNameIgnoreCase(String name);
    List<User> findByStatusOrderByAgeDesc(Status status);
}

Usage:

List<User> adults = userRepository.findByAgeGreaterThan(18);
List<User> namedJohn = userRepository.findByNameIgnoreCase("john");
List<User> sorted = userRepository.findByStatusOrderByAgeDesc(Status.ACTIVE);
